sql:
SELECT dataset_id, dataset_name, description, source
FROM economic_datasets
WHERE region_id = 1 AND country_id = 3 AND economic_sector_id = 2;

SELECT c.country_name
FROM countries c
JOIN economic_datasets ed ON c.country_id = ed.country_id;

external_knowledge:
Economic snapshot refers to a summary of the current state of a country's economy, including key indicators such as GDP and inflation rate; 
GDP (Gross Domestic Product) is a widely used indicator of a country's economic performance, representing the total value of goods and services produced within its borders; 
Inflation rate is a measure of how quickly prices for goods and services are rising in an economy.

sql:
SELECT ed.dataset_name, ed.description, ed.source, ds.url, ds.last_updated, ds.data_frequency
FROM economic_datasets AS ed
INNER JOIN data_sources AS ds ON ed.source = ds.source_name;

SELECT economic_sector_id, COUNT(*) as dataset_count
FROM economic_datasets
GROUP BY economic_sector_id;

SELECT es.sector_name
FROM economic_sectors es
JOIN economic_datasets ed ON es.economic_sector_id = ed.economic_sector_id;
